Iowa Beef Processors Inc is lifting alockout at its Dakota City, Nebraska, processing plant andplans to resume operations March 16, United Food and CommercialWorkers (UFCW) Union spokesman Allen Zack said.    Iowa Beef mailed a letter to members of UFCW Local 222informing them a lockout imposed by the company December 14would be lifted and meatpackers could return to work under IowaBeef's "revised, last and best final offer," Zack said.    Iowa Beef had closed the plant indefinitely in mid-Decemberbecause it said it had no alternative to threats by meatpackersto disrupt operations.    About 2,800 members of Local 222 are affected by theshutdown. A 3-1/2 year labor contract at the plant expiredDecember 13. Reuter&#3;